Darebin Falcons Logo
The Darebin Women’s Sports Club, nicknamed the Falcons, is based in the northern suburbs of Melbourne and primarily notable for its Australian rules football team which competes in the highest-level Victorian state league – the VFL Women’s. It is the only VFLW club that is not affiliated with a side from the national AFL Women’s competition or the Australian Football League. Founded in 1990, the club originally competed in the Victorian Women’s Football League.
